{{Quote|Cem would be the Fels' shadow child.''"<br />"''Shadow child?''"<br />"''Publicly unacknowledged. Secret, in fact. It's a common Chiss precaution to keep enemies from wiping out an entire ruling family.|Chaf'orm'bintrano and Luke Skywalker|<ref name="The Joiner King" />}}
'''Shadow child''' was a [[Chiss family/Legends|family]] rank of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]]. A child born to an important family, whose birth and identity were kept secret to prevent the entire bloodline being exterminated by rivals.

[[Baron/Legends|Baron]] [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]] and his wife [[Syal Antilles Fel]] were said to have had five children, but evidence existed for a total of six: four sons, [[Chak Fel|Chak]], [[Davin Fel|Davin]], [[Jagged Fel|Jagged]], and [[Cem Fel|Cem]], and two daughters, [[Cherith Fel|Cherith]] and [[Wynssa Fel|Wynssa]]. Cem was revealed to be a shadow child of the [[Fel dynasty|Fel family]].<ref name="The Joiner King">''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]''</ref>

{{Chiss-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The only recorded allusion to the custom was made in order to explain an apparent paradox in the Fel family. The introduction of the character [[Chak Fel]] in ''[[Survivor's Quest]]'' in [[2004]] created a continuity error by adding a sixth Fel child when five Fel children &mdash; five having been established as the total number of Fel children &mdash; had already been identified. As [[Davin Fel]] was the only Fel child of similar age to Chak, [[Lucas Licensing]] editor [[Sue Rostoni]] initially suggested that Chak was in fact Davin, with Chak being a nickname.<ref name="Sue">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=93010&start=5475#6053973|thread=Welcome some BCaT VIPs|user=[[Sue Rostoni|Eeusu Estornii]]|date=2005-03-05|time=11:09 AM}}</ref> This suggestion was ultimately not integrated into [[canon]], with ''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]'' introducing the "shadow child" custom as an explanation.<ref name="The Joiner King" />

While it may be that "shadow children" were a true Chiss custom, it is also possible that the explanation was supplied as misinformation to disguise the true reason for this discrepancy.

